## Priority: Interactive Buffer Context

The primary use case is helping while working in a specific file. Essential queries:
- Current buffer filename
- Point position (line and column number)
- Active region content (if any selection exists)
- Buffer mode/language

Workflow: User presses a keybinding in Emacs that invokes pi for help. Pi can then use the emacsclient extension to interrogate the current context interactively - "what file am I in?", "what's selected?", "what's the error on this line?", etc.

This enables a tight feedback loop where pi understands exactly what the user is looking at without manual copy-paste.
